"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The lineplot function from seaborn expects the 'data' parameter to be a DataFrame or a long-form dataset. In this case, 'data=None' is incorrect. Additionally, the x parameter should be a 1D array, but 'df['X'].values.reshape(-1, 1)' is a 2D array. This will cause an error when trying to plot.\", \"patch\": \"20c20\\n< sb.lineplot(data=None, x=df['X'].values.reshape(-1, 1), y=Y_pred)\\n---\\n> sb.lineplot(data=df_new, x='X', y=Y_pred.flatten())\\n\"}"